Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: RMW, RPR: Erin Drost, CLERK: E. Ferrill, ADA:  Michael Edward Nieskes,  DF ATTY:  Joseph R. Caton, DF:  Greggory Marquie A C Rosenbloom did not appear. Court lifts stay and issues warrant. Court issues warrant Statewide with a $250.00 purge provision.

CO: RMW, REP: Drost, CLERK: Liddle. ADA:  Alexis S. Mckinley   DF ATTY:  Joseph R. Caton   DF:  Greggory Marquie A C Rosenbloom did not appear. Case called at 10:15 a.m. Atty Caton  does not know where defendant is. ADA McKinley requesting for a stayed warrant. Court will issue a warrant and stay.  Return on warrant scheduled for November 30, 2015 at 01:00 pm.

It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO ABUSIVE CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, Erin M.  The term "abusive contact" is hereby defined as a verbal assault or an intentional infliction of or threat to inflict physical pain, physical injury or illness, an impairment of physical condition, and /or sexual contact or sexual intercourse without consent.  The aforementioned condition of bond/bail is set pursuant to Sec. 969.02(3)(d), Wis Stats.

Further, it is ordered that if the defendant fails to comply with the conditions of his/her bond/bail that he/she may be charged with the offense of bailjumping contrary to Sec. 946.49(1)(a), Wis Stats.
